The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence and President Emmanuel Macron during a state visit at the State Department in Washington, D.C. Pence emphasized the enduring friendship between the United States and France, highlighting their shared history and values. He praised Macron's leadership and the progress made by both countries under President Trump. Pence also mentioned the strong personal relationship between Macron and Trump. Macron expressed gratitude for the longstanding alliance between the two nations and emphasized the importance of their economic relations. He discussed the need for continued cooperation and investment to address future challenges. Both leaders toasted to the friendship between the United States and France.